title: MAC football power rankings: Not much movement in my better-late-than-never week five rankings
text:
While checking on the weather report this gray, dreary Friday afternoon it occurred to me that I never posted my updated Mid-Americn Conference football power rankings this week. 
Never did it. Just completely slipped my mind. Yikes. 
I typically publish my new rankings on Monday morning or early afternoon. Hmmm... I can't really remember what I would have been doing around that time... oh wait, that's right . 
So yeah, my apologies for that. Not that anyone would complain about the slightly-more-pressing basketball news to which I had to attend, of course. 
Anyway, here, in super diluted and abbreviated form, are my week five power rankings. I promise we'll be back to the full thing after this weekend's game. You know, unless Bruce Brown commits or something. 
And when you're done, you should go check out my week-five MAC picks , just because. 1. Toledo Last week: W, 37-7 vs. Arkansas State Previous rank: 1
